## Quickstart (dev mode — no infrastructure needed)

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 2. Configure your API key
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env: set LLM_API_KEY (and LLM_BASE_URL if not using the default)

# 3. Run
python agent.py
```

In dev mode the agent calls your LLM provider directly.
No GATE, no domain, no token required.

---

## Switch to prod mode

When you're ready to run inside ATOM with governance, auditing, and HITL:

1. Open atom-studio → create a domain → create an agent (wizard)
2. Copy the one-time token shown after agent creation
3. In your `.env`, set:
   ```
   ATOM_MODE=prod
   ATOM_GATE_URL=http://<your-gate-host>:8080
   ATOM_DOMAIN_ID=<domain-uuid>
   ATOM_AGENT_ID=<agent-uuid>
   ATOM_AGENT_JWT=<one-time-token>
   ATOM_MODEL_NAME={{.ModelName}}
   ```
4. Run: `python agent.py`

In prod mode:
- All LLM calls route through GATE (JWT-authenticated, OPA policy-checked, audited)
- HITL pauses go to the atom-studio approval queue
- Every call is appended to the immutable audit chain

